{
  "texts": [
    "The MSA is an extended version of the self-attentive mechanism, aiming to enhance the representation capability of the model.",
    "It applies the attention mechanism to multiple attention heads (i.e., multiple Q, K, and V).",
    "Each attention head within the MSA mechanism is capable of learning distinct weights, allowing it to focus on different information within the input sequence.",
    "Finally, the outputs from these multiple attention heads are combined or aggregated to produce the final representation vector.",
    "MSA is extensively employed in Transformer models to capture global dependencies present in the input sequence."
  ]
}